ANOTHER radio station in KZN has decided to shut its doors after one of the staff their members was tested positive for the coronavirus. The provincial community radio station Nongoma FM in Nongoma in KZN announced that from today, they will be playing 80% of music and suspends the broadcasts. Station manager Prince Sbo Zulu said that they received the information that one of the DJ's tested positive of Covid-19. "We have instructed all our staff members to stay at home and suspended all our normal broadcasts," said Zulu. He further said that they will also screen and test the staff. "This is difficult times for Mzansi. Please, let us stay safe," said Zulu.